cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper discusses the use of neural machine translation (NMT) systems to obtain continuous-space sentence representations, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training neural networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML), making cs.LG (Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper evaluates the learned sentence representations in classification and similarity tasks, which could involve computer vision (CV) and neural networks (NE), making these sub-categories also possible.
